  "text": "Five key files implement stack protection mechanisms in the llvm-project--a8f3c97d repository:\n\n1. **llvm/lib/CodeGen/StackProtector.cpp** — Implements the `StackProtector` FunctionPass (and `StackProtectorPass` for the new pass manager). This is the core LLVM CodeGen pass that analyzes functions for buffer-overflow risk and inserts stack canary checks (`__stack_chk_guard`/`__stack_chk_fail` calls) around vulnerable stack frames.\n\n2. **llvm/lib/CodeGen/SafeStack.cpp** — Defines the `SafeStack` class and `SafeStackLegacyPass`/`SafeStackPass`. This pass implements the SafeStack instrumentation that separates stack allocations into a 'safe' stack (not addressable by unsafe operations) and an 'unsafe' stack, protecting return addresses and local variables from overflow-based attacks.\n\n3. **llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/StackProtector.h** — The header declaring the `StackProtector` and `StackProtectorPass` class interfaces, including the `SSPLayoutKind` enum (NoSSP, SSPBasic, SSPStrong, SSPReq) used to classify stack frame protection requirements.\n\n4. **libc/src/compiler/generic/__stack_chk_fail.cpp** — The LLVM libc runtime implementation of `__stack_chk_fail()`, the function called at runtime when a stack canary mismatch is detected (i.e., a stack buffer overflow has corrupted the canary). This is the handler that terminates the program on stack smashing detection.\n\n5. **llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp** — Implements the `AddressSanitizer` instrumentation pass, which includes stack frame protection via poisoned redzones around stack allocations. It uses `ASanStackFrameLayout` to compute and insert shadow memory poisoning/unpoisoning around local variables to detect stack buffer overflows at runtime."
}

